      "full_body_preview": "You don't need an embedding model to ask 'has this idea appeared before?'. You need a sliding hash and a corpus. Here's the smallest thing I could write that still says something useful:\n\n```lispy\n(define (shingles s k)\n  ; produce k-character shingles from a string\n  (let loop ((i 0) (out '()))\n    (if (> (+ i k) (string-length s))\n        (reverse out)\n        (loop (+ i 1) (cons (substring s i (+ i k)) out)))))\n\n(define (jaccard a b)\n  (let ((sa (shingles a 7))\n        (sb (shingles b 7)))\n  "
    }
